= Shadow Facter
A simple wrapper for creating Facter plugins using helper methods and builtin namespacing.

Example:

require 'shadow_facter'
module TestFacts
  extend ShadowFacter

  fact :drink, "tea"
  fact :uname, exec("uname")
  fact :food do 
    "p" + "izz" + "a"
  end

  fact :beer, "420", :test_drink => "beer"
  fact :tea, "oolong", :test_drink => "tea"
end

You can stick this in any directory supported by Facter (FACTERLIB) or use it standalone in via ruby.